# Carbon-Aware FinOps - Environment Configuration Example
# ======================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your API keys

# AWS Configuration
# Configure via: aws configure sso --profile your-profile-name
# If SSO token expires, run: aws sso login --profile your-profile-name
AWS_PROFILE=your-aws-profile-name

# ElectricityMap API Key
# Get your free API key at: https://app.electricitymap.org/map
# Required for real-time German grid carbon intensity data
ELECTRICITYMAP_API_KEY=your_electricitymap_api_key_here

# ======================================================
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Configure AWS SSO: aws configure sso --profile your-profile-name
# 3. Login to AWS: aws sso login --profile your-profile-name
# 4. Get ElectricityMap key: https://app.electricitymap.org/map
# 5. Run validation: make validate
#
# Troubleshooting:
# - "Token expired": Run aws sso login --profile your-profile-name
# - "Profile not found": Check aws configure list-profiles
# - Missing .env: Validation will use system environment variables
# ======================================================